  "local_port": 42044,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I add question details digitally on Quora?",
  "response": "Adding detailed information to your questions on Quora can help attract more accurate and insightful answers from the community. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to add question details digitally on Quora:\n\n### 1. **Sign In to Your Quora Account**\n   - **Visit Quora:** Go to [Quora's website](https://www.quora.com/) using your preferred web browser.\n   - **Log In:** Click on the \"Log In\" button at the top right corner and enter your credentials. If you don't have an account, you'll need to sign up first.\n\n### 2. **Navigate to the \"Ask Question\" Interface**\n   - **Locate the Ask Button:** On the Quora homepage, find the \"Add Question\" or \"Ask Question\" button. This is usually prominently displayed near the top of the page, sometimes represented by a \"+\" icon.\n   - **Click to Begin:** Click on this button to open the question creation interface.\n\n### 3. **Enter Your Question Title**\n   - **Be Clear and Concise:** In the prompt that appears (e.g., \"What is your question?\"), type a clear and specific question. A well-formulated question captures attention and provides a foundation for effective answers.\n   - **Use Proper Formatting:** Capitalize appropriately and avoid unnecessary punctuation to ensure clarity.\n\n### 4. **Add Detailed Information in the Description**\n   - **Provide Context:** Below the question title, there is typically a larger text box for additional details. Use this space to elaborate on your question.\n     - **Explain the Background:** Share any relevant information that led you to ask the question. This might include personal experiences, specific scenarios, or prior research you've conducted.\n     - **Specify Requirements:** If you're looking for answers with certain criteria (e.g., experienced professionals, academic sources), mention them here.\n     - **Include Examples:** Providing examples can clarify what you're asking and help answerers understand your perspective.\n   - **Use Formatting Tools:**\n     - **Bold and Italics:** Highlight key points using bold or italics to make your details stand out.\n     - **Bullet Points or Numbered Lists:** Organize information clearly for better readability.\n     - **Hyperlinks:** If referencing external sources, include hyperlinks to provide direct access to more information.\n     - **Images and Media:** Enhance your question with relevant images, diagrams, or other media by clicking the image icon and uploading your files.\n\n### 5. **Select Relevant Topics**\n   - **Choose Appropriate Topics:** Quora allows you to categorize your question by selecting relevant topics. This helps in reaching the right audience who are knowledgeable in that area.\n   - **Add Multiple Topics:** You can add multiple topics to cover different aspects of your question, ensuring broader visibility.\n\n### 6. **Review and Preview Your Question**\n   - **Check for Clarity:** Read through your question and details to ensure they accurately convey what you're asking.\n   - **Proofread:** Look for grammatical errors or typos that might distract from your main points.\n   - **Preview Appearance:** If Quora provides a preview feature, use it to see how your question and details will appear to others.\n\n### 7. **Submit Your Question**\n   - **Click \"Submit\":** Once you're satisfied with your question and details, click the \"Submit\" or \"Ask\" button to post it publicly on Quora.\n   - **Monitor Responses:** After submission, keep an eye on incoming answers and engage with respondents by upvoting helpful answers or asking follow-up questions for clarification.\n\n### 8. **Editing Your Question (If Needed)**\n   - **Access Your Question:** Navigate to your profile and find the question you've posted.\n   - **Click \"Edit\":** Select the \"Edit\" option to modify the title or details.\n   - **Make Necessary Changes:** Update any information to improve clarity or add new context.\n   - **Save Changes:** After editing, ensure you save to update the public view of your question.\n\n### **Additional Tips for Adding Effective Question Details**\n- **Be Specific:** Vague questions receive vague answers. The more specific you are, the better the quality of responses.\n- **Stay On Topic:** Ensure that your details are relevant to the main question to avoid confusing potential answerers.\n- **Maintain a Polite Tone:** A respectful and considerate tone encourages more people to engage with your question.\n- **Avoid Overloading Information:** While details are important, too much information can be overwhelming. Balance comprehensiveness with readability.\n\nBy following these steps and tips, you can effectively add comprehensive details to your questions on Quora, increasing the likelihood of receiving informative and helpful responses from the community.",
